there is a top five percent in every industry that lead innovation and dialogue: from doctors to teachers to poets to programmers. they get there because they have discipline, they have love for what they do, they have courage, and they work tirelessly to hone their talent and skills...

when you see a five percent relationship it is truly inspiring. we all know people who fit into this category. and we know many more who unfortunately do not. that does not mean the five percent relationships do not require work. in fact it is the work and communication that builds a five percent foundation.

the five percent rule... a random, short mu i was speaking with my friend about what he calls the five percent rule. i found it really motivating. it applies to most things in life. five percent of people are the most successful, have the most money, are pioneers, are the most passionate, drive real change...

the five percent rule applies to relationships as well. i would say only about five percent of relationships are truly amazing. fifty-five percent of marriages now end in divorce. how many people stick it out because of kids? money? familiarity? routine? fear of the unknown? insecurities? then there is the five percent .

it is rare but so are most things in life that are worth having (including number bitcoin). the five percent rule reminds me of one of my absolute favorite quotes by ralph waldo emerson: "make the most of yourself. for that is all there is of you." thanks to my friend cody for the inspo!
